HEADWORD: Transpadane
<hw>Trans"pa*dane`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>transpadanus</ets>; <ets>trans</ets> across + <ets>Padus</ets> the
Po.]</ety> <def>Lying or being on the further side of the river Po with
reference to Rome, that is, on the north side; -- opposed to
<xex>cispadane</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transpalatine</ent>⟦br⟧
